           SPELL=poster
         VERSION=20050907
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.tar.bz2
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/printing/${SOURCE}
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
      SOURCE_GPG="gurus.gpg:${SOURCE}.sig"
       BUILD_API=2
        KEYWORDS="printer"
        WEB_SITE=http://directory.fsf.org/poster.html
         ENTERED=20020405
         UPDATED=20020420
           SHORT="PostScript utility which resizes PS files"
cat << EOF
Poster is a PostScript utility which resizes PS files, potentially to split 
them into smaller pieces that are printable on normal paper sheets (e.g., 
printing an A1 poster on A4 pages). It has various options for specifying 
input and output page size and cut margins and to select tile pages to print.
EOF
